    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.2: \"Dendritic Ephexin5 levels are reduced in response to increased neural activity\"\n- \"After 2-3 days of expression, we found that E5-GFP was present in the dendrite and concentrated in dendritic spines (Fig. 2A). T\"\n\nFig.3: \"Ephexin5-GFP is enriched at sites of new spine outgrowth\"\n- \"Remarkably, we also found that E5-GFP was enriched on the dendrite at sites of new spine outgrowth, even 20 min before the appearance of the new spine (G/R 0.044 ± 0.006; p < 0.001; Fig. 3A, B). \". Experimental description: - \"Organotypic hippocampal slice cultures were prepared as described (Stoppini et al., 1991) from postnatal day (P)6-7 Sprague-Dawley rats...\"\n- Species of overexpressed Ephexin5; Arhgef15; Kiaa0915 is not stated in the paper. Authors were contacted for additional information. Answer:\n\n\"Dear Pim van Nierop,\nAndrew Hamilton, lead author of the paper, says that the species is mouse.\nAll the best,\nKaren and Andrew\"",
